                    <desc>
                      <locus target="#127v" facs="130"> f. 127v, bottom, in pencil, in a crude hand</locus>): Hymn to Saint Ewosṭatewos.
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a4">
                    <desc type="RecordTransaction">
                      <locus target="#128v" facs="131">Fol. 128v</locus>: Record of land transaction in 1919 EC with witnesses listed. 19 lines in column 1
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a5">
                    <desc type="RecordTransaction">
                      <locus target="#128v" facs="131"> f. 128v, bottom four lines</locus>: Record of lending of money
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a6">
                    <desc>
                      <locus target="#iir(ecto)" facs="002">Fol. iir(ecto)</locus>Notes on court administration, in crude hand, in pencil
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a7">
                    <desc type="RecordTransaction">
                    <locus target="#127v #128v" facs="130 131"> f. 127v, 128v, col.2</locus>, Notes on land transaction
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a8">
                    <desc type="RecordTransaction">
                    <locus target="#129v" facs="132">Fol. 129v</locus> Notes on the transaction of the manuscript
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <desc>
                      <locus target="#ir(ecto)" facs="001">Fol. ir(ecto)</locus> Title of the book and pen trial
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <desc>
                      <locus target="#51v" facs="054">Fol. 51v</locus> a small cross, written in red ink in a later hand, marks the midpoint of the Psalms
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <desc>
                      <locus target="#129r" facs="131">Fol. 129r</locus> Scrawls
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <desc>
                    Numbered quires: quires 3–10
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <desc>
                    Notes in a later hand found throughout
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e6">
                    <desc>
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#2r #4v #9r #16v #26v" facs="004 007 011 019 029">folss. 2r, 4v, 9r, 16v, 26v, </locus>, etc.);
                      and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#1v #12v #16r #17r #45r" facs="004 015 018 019 047">1v, 12v, 16r, 17r, 45r, </locus>, etc.);
                      erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#67r #67v #70r #90r" facs="069 070 072 092">67r, 67v, 70r, 90r, </locus>, etc.);
                      text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#21v #22r #22v #25r #26v" facs="024 025 027 029">21v, 22r, 22v, 25r, 26v</locus>)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e7">
                    <desc>
                      <locus target="#102v" facs="105"> f. 102v, line 3</locus>: a line of text is written interlinearly as well as being
                      visible, though partially erased, in the upper margin
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e8">
                    <desc>
                      The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line.
                      Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an
                      appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate
                      script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe
                      completes the line of text above or below the end of the line (throughout). This scribe also will reduce the font size at the end of
                    lines to avoid having to go onto the next line (e.g., <locus target="#43v #44r #45v" facs="046 048">fols. 43v, 44r, 45v</locus>)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                      </list>
